The paper discusses the development of cyber-physical system scenarios and their security, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of collaborative events to explore challenges and develop solutions suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of a shared CPS testbed platform, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the evaluation of the success of the process suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
